tissueExpression.summary: General cytoplasmic expression, most abundant in endothelial cells and placental trophoblasts.

subcellularLocation.summary: Mainly localized to the microtubules. In addition localized to the Golgi apparatus & nucleus.

tissueExpression.summary: Weak to moderate cytoplasmic immunoreactivity was observed in most normal tissues, in some cases accentuated to the nuclear membrane. Pancreatic islets, urothelial cells and trophoblastic cells were strongly stained.
tissueExpression.validation: Mainly consistent with RNA expression data

image.description: Immunohistochemical staining of human pancreas shows strong cytoplasmic positivity in islet cells.

tissueExpression.summary: Most tumour cells were negative. Testicular cancers and a few cases of endometrial, ovarian and breast cancers displayed moderate to strong cytoplasmic immunoreactivity.
